observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Local Chief Executive direct the:

a.	Municipal Engineer to closely monitor and pursue the timely and full implementation of the projects;

b.	Bids and Awards Committee to follow the time schedule for advertisement/posting, submission and receipt/opening of bids, award of contract and contract signing in the APP, to facilitate the implementation of priority projects and maximize the utilization of government resources;

c.	Municipal Planning and Development Coordinator to conduct efficient planning, monitoring and evaluation on the implementation of different projects of the municipality, to avoid delay and adjustment in the implementation; and

d.	Local Finance Committee concerned to comply with the posting of the quarterly report of LGSF-SBDP of the NTF-ELCAC pursuant to Local Budget Circular No. 151 dated March 30, 2023.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive direct the responsible officers to ensure the following:

The Municipal Engineer to intensify the monitoring of all on-going projects to avoid unjustified delays in compliance with the approved contract and to impose appropriate actions and remedies to erring contractors; 

Forfeit performance security in accordance with the provisions of the contract;

Take over the contract or award the contract to a qualified contractor through negotiation; and 

The Municipal Accountant to issue Order of Payment for Liquidated Damages as determined and recommended by the Engineer.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor install control and monitoring mechanisms to ensure that the use of government vehicles and consumption of fuel shall strictly be for a valid public purpose.  Henceforth, the following documents and reports should be required on the use of government vehicles and fuel consumption:
Serially numbered Driver’s Trip Tickets approved by the Municipal Mayor or his authorized representative to control the use of government vehicle;
Monthly Report of Official Travels prepared by the driver concerned and Monthly Equipment Utilization Report prepared by the equipment custodian summarizing in chronological order his trips or use of equipment, respectively, for the month, duly certified by the driver and approved by the Administrative Officer;
Report of Fuel Consumption shall be prepared and submitted monthly to the auditor for verification purposes.  The report shall show the different types of motor vehicles utilized by the agency during the month, total distance traveled, total fuel consumed and the normal fuel consumption for each vehicle; and
Submit to the Audit Team the “Bill For” used in the purchase of fuel, oil and lubricants for the period CY 2019.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor instruct the:
Municipal Treasurer to conduct intensive tax campaign and information drive in order to encourage more taxpayers to pay taxes;
Coordinate with the SB to appropriate funds for the expenses related to tax campaigns and collection;
Impose the legal remedies provided for, and exercise its taxing authority mandated under the Local Government Code of 1991; and
Municipal Accountant and Municipal Treasurer to reconcile the RPT and SET receivable balances.
